{"pageProps":{"data":{"news_id":"713","news_catgory":"1","hot_news":"0","news_push":"","news_on_top":"1","news_title":"氣候危機下 2019年化石燃料補貼仍近5000億美元","news_summary":"","image_path":"","news_des":null,"news_content":"<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>2020-06-09&nbsp; 22:17&nbsp; </span><span style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>中央社<span lang='EN-US'>/</span>巴黎<span lang='EN-US'>9</span>日綜合外電報導</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'><img alt='' src='/user_files/news_files/%E7%9F%B3%E5%8C%96%E7%87%83%E6%96%99%E8%A3%9C%E8%B2%BC.JPG' style='width: 800px; height: 509px;' />&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>國際能源總署（<span lang='EN-US'>IEA</span>）與經濟合作暨發展組織（<span lang='EN-US'>OECD</span>）聯合發布的報告指出，儘管全球陷入氣候危機，<span lang='EN-US'>2019</span>年各國政府對化石燃料的補貼仍高達將近<span lang='EN-US'>5000</span>億美元。美聯社</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>國際能源總署（<span lang='EN-US'>IEA</span>）與經濟合作暨發展組織（<span lang='EN-US'>OECD</span>）聯合發布的報告指出，儘管全球陷入氣候危機，<span lang='EN-US'>2019</span>年各國政府對化石燃料的補貼仍高達將近<span lang='EN-US'>5000</span>億美元。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>不過根據<span lang='EN-US'>IEA</span>數據，單論各國政府對於消耗化石燃料的補貼，<span lang='EN-US'>2019</span>年跟<span lang='EN-US'>2018</span>年相比減少<span lang='EN-US'>1200</span>億美元或<span lang='EN-US'>27%</span>，主因石油和天然氣價格下滑。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>大力支持使用石油與天然氣的政府，包括伊朗、沙烏地阿拉伯、中國、俄羅斯、印尼、埃及、印度與委內瑞拉等。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>OECD</span><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>通報，與此同時，去年<span lang='EN-US'>44</span>個富裕和新興經濟體對生產化石燃料的補貼則增加<span lang='EN-US'>38%</span>，來到<span lang='EN-US'>550</span>億美元。補貼形式包括現金、減稅和其他信用貸款。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>IEA</span><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>與<span lang='EN-US'>OECD</span>上週結束前發布聯合聲明表示，去年<span lang='EN-US'>77</span>個經濟體對於消費和生產化石燃料的補貼總計<span lang='EN-US'>4780</span>億美元，比<span lang='EN-US'>2018</span>年下滑<span lang='EN-US'>18%</span>。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>燃燒石油、天然氣和煤碳占了地球基本能源使用的<span lang='EN-US'>8</span>成以上，且是導致地球暖化的溫室氣體的主要來源。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>各國政府早就承認，有必要停止支持化石燃料的生產與使用。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='font-family: &quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif;'>資料來源：<span lang='EN-US'>https://udn.com/news/story/6811/4624826</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","keyword":"","news_order_id":"0","create_date":"2020-06-11","clk_count":"306"}},"__N_SSG":true}